  "description": "bodyFreq=62Hz (B♭) — the decisive application of OWL-I. 62Hz clashes with C. When you play in C major, the body is wrong. When you play in B♭, the body is right. This preset has no key. The odd dividers ÷3, ÷7 amplify the strangeness: ÷3 adds a subharmonic fifth that collides, ÷7 adds a seventh-partial that belongs to no Western tuning. This is Flux because it never resolves. Everything is mid-collision. Play major scales and hear them bent.",
